\lim_{n \to \infty} \exp(\ln(n^{1/n})) = \lim_{n \to \infty} \exp(\frac{\ln(n)}{n}) = \lim_{n \to \infty} \exp\left( \lim_{n \to \infty}\frac{\ln(n)'}{n'} \right) = \lim_{n \to \infty} \exp\left( \lim_{n \to \infty}1/n \right) = \lim_{n \to \infty} \exp(0) = 1
